cv original:
Lucas Durand - Belgium - Male - 25
Experience:
- Junior Analyst at Deloitte Belgium (1 year): Prepared detailed financial reports, conducted market and industry analysis, collaborated in client workshops, assisted in audit preparations, maintained databases of client information, conducted competitor benchmarking. Participated in weekly strategy meetings with senior consultants. Used Excel to develop models for cost optimization, presented findings in client presentations. Supported cross-functional teams with ad hoc research tasks.
- Business Consultant Intern at PwC (6 months): Contributed to process improvement projects for a multinational client. Drafted documentation, mapped workflows, identified inefficiencies, suggested practical solutions. Assisted in developing presentation decks, participated in client calls, summarized discussions for internal use. Worked on data visualization projects using Tableau to present findings to non-technical stakeholders.
Education:
- Master in Management, Solvay Brussels School, 2025 (expected): Courses included Corporate Finance, Business Strategy, Leadership, Operations Management, Marketing Analytics, Strategic Management. Group projects included market entry strategy for a European retail company, operational efficiency study for a manufacturing client. Received distinction for thesis on optimization of internal business processes using data analytics.
- Bachelor in Economics, University of Brussels, 2021: Coursework in Microeconomics, Macroeconomics, Quantitative Methods, International Trade, Corporate Finance. Completed capstone project analyzing the financial health and growth potential of Belgian SMEs. Participated in student exchange program at University of Amsterdam focusing on European financial regulations.
Skills: Financial Analysis, Excel (advanced modeling, macros), PowerPoint (professional reports), Data Visualization (Tableau, Power BI), Strategic Planning, Problem Solving, Team Collaboration, Communication
Projects:
- Operational Efficiency Study: Collected workflow data from multiple departments, identified bottlenecks, proposed process improvements, presented findings in board meetings, documented implementation roadmap.
- Strategic Market Analysis: Evaluated new market entry opportunities, presented recommendations with cost-benefit analysis, created Excel dashboards for scenario modeling.
Languages: French (native), English (fluent), Dutch (basic)
Certifications: Lean Six Sigma Green Belt, CFA Level 1 Candidate
Hobbies: Competitive cycling including participation in national events, photography of urban architecture and landscapes, organizing local charity events for underprivileged youth, reading economic journals
Achievements:
- Winner of internal Solvay Case Competition 2023
- Recognition for highest thesis grade in Master program
References:
- Marie Lefevre, Senior Consultant at Deloitte, marie.lefevre@deloitte.com
- Thomas Van Houtte, Manager at PwC, thomas.vanhoutte@pwc.com

cv original:
Lucas Pereira
Brazilian · Male · 23 years old
Target MSc: Management / Strategy

EDUCATION
Bachelor in Business Administration
Fundação Getulio Vargas (FGV), São Paulo
2019 – 2023

Core coursework in strategy, corporate finance, marketing, operations and economics

Strong quantitative training with applied projects in market analysis and financial decision-making

Graduated from one of Brazil’s top-ranked business schools, known for analytical rigor and selectivity

PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE

Business Analyst Intern – Itaú Unibanco, São Paulo
July 2023 – December 2023

Conducted market, financial and customer data analyses to support decision-making for retail banking products

Analyzed product profitability, customer acquisition costs and revenue drivers across different client segments

Designed and maintained Excel dashboards to track key performance indicators (KPIs) such as customer acquisition, retention and cross-selling

Collaborated with senior analysts and product managers to prepare management presentations and performance reports

Contributed to data-driven recommendations aimed at improving product positioning and operational efficiency

Strategy Intern – Ambev (AB InBev Group)
January 2023 – June 2023

Supported pricing and commercial strategy for FMCG products across multiple brands and distribution channels

Conducted competitor benchmarking, analyzing price positioning, promotions and market shares

Performed market sizing and demand analysis to assess growth opportunities in selected regions

Assisted in building financial scenarios to evaluate the impact of pricing and volume changes on revenue and margins

Worked closely with strategy and commercial teams in a multinational environment

Student Consultant – FGV Junior Enterprise
2021 – 2022

Participated in consulting projects for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in retail and logistics sectors

Conducted diagnostic analyses of clients’ business models, cost structures and operational processes

Developed market studies and strategic recommendations focused on growth, pricing and process optimization

Presented findings and actionable recommendations directly to clients’ management teams

SKILLS

Technical Skills

Excel (advanced spreadsheets, dashboards, basic financial models)

PowerPoint (structured presentations, executive summaries)

Basic SQL (data extraction and simple queries)

Analytical Skills

Market analysis and competitive intelligence

Financial analysis and basic financial modeling

Strategic problem structuring

Languages

Portuguese: Native

English: Fluent

Spanish: Intermediate

PERSONAL INTERESTS
Football, macroeconomics, entrepreneurship, endurance running

EDUCATION BSc in Statistics and Data Science University of Michigan, Ann Arbor 2020 – 2024

Core coursework: Probability Theory, Applied Regression, Database Management, and Machine Learning.

Capstone Project: Developed a predictive model for local retail demand using Python and historical weather data.

Member of the Michigan Data Science Team (MDST).

PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE

Data Analyst Intern – Amazon (Operations), Seattle May 2024 – August 2024

Developed SQL queries to extract and clean large-scale shipment data from AWS Redshift.

Presented weekly performance metrics to the Operations Director.

Supported the procurement team in managing relationships with Tier-1 suppliers during global chip shortages.

Automated the inventory tracking system using Python, replacing manual Excel spreadsheets and reducing errors by 20%.

SKILLS

Technical: Python (Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn), R, SQL, Tableau, Power BI, Git.

Analytical: Predictive modeling, Optimization, Statistical hypothesis testing.

Languages: English (Native), Spanish (Intermediate).

PERSONAL INTERESTS Chess (National ranking), Backpacking (completed the Appalachian Trail), Jazz Piano.

EDUCATION Bachelor of Business Studies (BBS) Trinity College Dublin 2020 – 2024

Specialization in Innovation and Digital Business.

Winner of the "LaunchBox" Student Accelerator program for a fintech startup concept.

Core coursework: Venture Capital, Digital Strategy, Lean Startup Methodology.

PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE

Product Management Intern – Stripe, Dublin May 2024 – August 2024

Collaborated with engineering and design teams to refine the user onboarding flow for small businesses.

Managed a team of 5 student developers and oversaw a micro-marketing budget of €500/month.

Successfully pitched the project to local angel investors, securing seed funding for technical scaling.

SKILLS

Technical: Agile/Scrum (Jira), Figma (UI/UX design), Python (Basic), Google Analytics.

Analytical: Product-market fit analysis, Growth hacking, User interview synthesis.

Languages: English (Native), Irish (Fluent), French (B2).

PERSONAL INTERESTS Podcast production (Tech & Society), Ultramarathon running, Chess.
